<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kylie Minogue stunned fans this week with a retro themed performance of her new single Say Something on The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon.</p>

<p>The rendition featured an array of vintage special effects that made it appear as if Kylie was performing in the 1970s or '80s. </p>

<p>After it aired, fans flocked to YouTube to praise the star for her nostalgic retro concept.</p>

<p>She's back! Kylie Minogue stunned fans this week with a retro themed performance of her new single Say Something on The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon</p>

<p>'I wasn’t born in the 70s, but I bet this is how 70s television felt like. What a great performance!' gushed one.</p>

<p>Another wrote: 'Omg doesn't she look amazing. Proper 80s vibe disco effects.'</p>

<p>'Wow, finally she is giving us a different visual aesthetic,' exclaimed another.</p>

<p>Kylie later took to Twitter to reveal the secrets behind the retro performance.</p>

<p>Vintage: The rendition featured an array of vintage special effects that made it appear as if Kylie was performing in the 1970s or '80s</p>

<p>'I wasn’t born in the 70s, but I bet this is how 70s television felt like. What a great performance!' gushed one fan </p>

<p>Not only did she use a green screen for the effects, she also filmed the performance with an old 1980s BBC news camera.</p>

<p>To ensure she looked the part, Kylie donned a vintage Antony Price dress from 1983.</p>

<p>Last month, the Princess of Pop detailed her experience filming the music video for her new single Say Something entirely in front of a green screen amid COVID-19 restrictions.</p>

<p>'It was a different shoot with the restrictions but it felt good to be back on set,' the songstress told The Herald Sun.</p>

<p>Revealed: Kylie used a green screen and filmed the performance on an old 1980s BBC news camera to achieve the vintage effect</p>

<p>In the clip, Kylie rides a horse statue as a salute to Bianca Jagger, who famously rode a white horse on the Studio 54 dance floor.</p>

<p>'The horse was the star of the show. I don't think my galactic steed was designed to be ridden, but I fell in love with him, he was gorgeous,' she said.</p>

<p>'I hope when people see it, it takes them to another level and away to wherever their happy place is.'</p>

<p>Kylie will release her fifteenth studio album Disco on November 6.</p>

<p>Coming soon: Say Something is the first single from Kylie's upcoming album, Disco, due out November 6</p>
